Given a collection of peers in a local image of pk, the  jointranking scheme ranks all the peers once based on their  outgoing bandwidth, and then based on their estimated delay from a target peer pi.
When a gossip message arrives at each peer , an image maintenance scheme integrates new records into the current local image and discards excess records such that certain property of the local image is improved ( e.g. , increase overall utility of peers in the image ) Aggregate performance of 45 a gossip mechanism can be presented by two average metrics and their distribution 